description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Specialty Doctor Maxillofacial and Oral Surgery &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration: 12 months (date) until (end date if known)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based Royal Gwent Hospital, Newport, SE Wales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time (10 Sessions)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date for Applications: Midnight on 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a locum Speciality Doctor post in Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery based at the Royal Gwent Hospital, Newport with sessions in Nevill Hall Hospital Abergavenny and Grange University Hospital when it opens this year (2020). The post is available with immediate effect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The existing department in the Royal Gwent Hospital has been open for 22 years, with the more recent addition of day care facilities, including a dedicated ward. There are six consultation rooms, surgeries and two operating theatres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join the 3 existing Consultants, 1 Specialist Registrar, 1 Core Trainee, 5 Specialty Doctors and 8 Junior Doctors in the provision of the specialist and routine oral and maxillofacial surgery services within the department. A full range of Oral and Maxillofacial surgery is carried with a complement of 10 inpatient beds and a dedicated theatre. Close relationships are maintained with ENT, Radiotherapy and Dermatological Departments. There is an active Postgraduate Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Free parking is available across all Aneurin Bevan University Health Board Sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those wishing to discuss the post informally in the first instance or visit the department should contact Mrs Angharad Brown, Clinical Director and Consultant Orthodontist 01633 238937.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position involves Regulated Activity with &lt;strong&gt;children and adults&lt;/strong&gt; as defined by the Safeguarding Vulnerable Groups Act (amended by the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012) and the following checks will be undertaken following any conditional offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an adults and children’s barred list check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be fully registered with the GDC and shall have ideally completed 4 years full time postgraduate training (or its equivalent gained on a part time or flexible basis) since first obtaining registration, including adequate experience in the specialty; or shall have equivalent experience and competencies. Possession of MFDSRCS, or MJDFRCS or FDSRCS would be advantageous&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy Ref: 040-LSD106 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date for Applications: Midnight on 11th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Published on NHS Jobs and Trac: 29th October 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
